### Book Manager REST API Tests
### Use this file with VS Code REST Client extension or Postman

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/books

### Get All Books
GET {{baseUrl}}
Accept: application/json

### Get Book by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/1
Accept: application/json

### Create a New Book
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Clean Code",
  "author": "Robert C. Martin"
}

### Create Another Book
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Effective Java",
  "author": "Joshua Bloch"
}

### Update Book by ID
PUT {{baseUrl}}/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Clean Code Updated",
  "author": "Robert C. Martin"
}

### Delete Book by ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/1

### Get All Books After Operations
GET {{baseUrl}}
Accept: application/json
